  "text": "Lung type II alveolar cell is regard as the protective barrier of lung and osmilphilic multilamellar body is a key structure in the type II alveolar cell to maintain cellular homeostasis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . As shown in Figure 6A , normal lung type II alveolar cell (blue arrow) was exerted in the LGS blocks NF-κB p65 translocation from cytoplasm to nuclear. RAW 264.7 cells were stimulated with LPS (1 μg/ml) for 2 h, incubated with or without LGS (400 μg/ml) for 24 h and observed by confocal microscopy. (200 ×) (B). Expression of NF-κB p65 in nuclear was detected by western blotting (C) and NF-κB nuclear binding activity was measured by EMSA (D).",
